The model shown here contained a combined driver's cabin and dining car area separated by an engine space. The train ran on metal tracks and the set also contained a buildable railway platform and 11 minifigures. Originally from 1991, this model was one of the few sets to be relaunched with completely new packaging as part of the LEGO Legends series in 2001."-- From employee gift re-creation (set 4002016-1-s4) building instructions.

name: Maersk Sealand Container Ship 2004 Edition
description: This version was limited to 14,000 sets (4,000 produced for Maersk Sealand and 10,000 unnumbered sets sold via LEGO [email protected]). The set used the last of LEGO's original supply of Maersk Blue ABS supply.For the 2005 version, which is identical in all respect except packaging and using a newer Maersk Blue ABS supply, see set 10152-2. For the 2006 version, which alters the stickers to reflect a corporate name change, see set 10152-3. For the 2010 re-release, see set 10155-1.

name: Maersk Sealand Container Ship 2005 Edition
description: Identical to 10152-1 except for "2005 Edition" on the box cover. Due to use of a newer stock of Maersk Blue ABS pellets (funded by Maersk), the shade of Maersk Blue in this version may vary from all previous Maersk sets including 10152-1. Original LEGO plans were a Dark Blue or Dark Green re-color of the 2004 version (never produced).For the 2004 version, which is identical in all respect except packaging and using a older Maersk Blue ABS supply, see set 10152-1. For the 2006 version, which alters the stickers to reflect a corporate name change, see set 10152-3. For the 2010 re-release, see set 10155-1.

Due to dwindling supply of needed parts, later runs of this set replaced the four 3001 2x4 Maersk Blue bricks with four 3001a 2x4 Maersk Blue bricks provided by LEGO model shops.For the 2004 version, with "Maersk Sealand" stickers and using a older Maersk Blue ABS supply, see set 10152-1. For the 2005 version, with "Maersk Sealand" stickers and using the newer Maersk Blue ABS supply, see set 10152-2. For the 2010 re-release, see set 10155-1.

name: Emerald Night
description: Included in the K10194-1 kit, which includes all Power Functions parts needed to convert this set into a remote controllable, motorized version. This kit also provides track for this train to be operated upon. Instructions for making these modifications are included in the set's building instructions."This original special edition model was launched in 2009 and is regarded by many as one of the most iconic LEGO trains ever created. Based upon an A3 Pacific steam locomotive, it took over a year and a half to be developed and included new, larger wheels and many other LEGO elements in new and rare colours. The original set did not contain any tracks but could be motorized by adding Power Functions."-- From employee gift re-creation (set 4002016-1-s5) building instructions.N.B.: The boxart reflects 1085 pieces. The difference reflects differences in how Rebrickable inventories the train wheel elements.

name: Republic Dropship with AT-OT
description: Flying through the skies of hostile planets, the Republic LAAT/c (Low Altitude Assault Transport/carrier) Dropship swoops down and deploys the AT-OT (All Terrain Open Transport) troop carrier for attacks on Separatist strongholds. Dropship features an opening cockpit, rotating front and rear cannons, auto-firing missiles and armament bay, and a fold-away handle on top. AT-OT features poseable legs, rotating cannons, crew compartment with weapon racks, and folding cockpit and boarding ramp. Drop ship automatically locks onto walker, then releases it with the push of a switch! Also holds the 7675-1 AT-TE Walker and the 8098-1 Clone Turbo Tank. Includes 2 clone pilots and 6 clone troopers. (From LEGO.com)

name: Grand Carousel
description: It’s a wonderful day for a ride on the merry-go-round! This elegant and beautifully detailed LEGO model isn’t just for show – it really spins and plays music while the horses and swing boats move up and down! Built with intricate, lifelike ornaments and features, the Grand Carousel is a spectacular addition to any LEGO display or carousel collection. Includes 9 minifigures and LEGO Power Functions motor and sound brick. Measures over 12” (30 cm) x 12” (30 cm) x over 12” (30 cm). (From LEGO.com)

name: Fire Brigade
description: Ding ding ding! There’s a fire in town! The fire brigade drives to the scene from this detailed and realistic 1930’s fire station. Designed to fit with other modular buildings like 10182 Café Corner and 10185 Green Grocer, the station features rare LEGO® pieces and innovative construction techniques. It includes a ‘30s-style fire truck, 4 minifigures, a fire-dog, an opening station garage door, and a removable building roof for interior access. It also includes 2 fully-furnished floors with fire-fighting tools, racks for the firemen’s helmets, fire-pole, ping-pong table, kitchen with fully-stocked fridge, couch, bookshelf and a roof with a water tower and bell. Measures 14″ (35 cm) high and 10″ (25 cm) wide. (From LEGO.com)

name: Tantive IV
description: The Star Wars™ saga begins! Blasting through space with Darth Vader’s Star Destroyer in pursuit, the Tantive IV blockade runner carries Princess Leia, C-3PO and R2-D2 on a vital mission for the Rebel Alliance. Celebrate the entire Star Wars saga with this all-new version of the very first starship seen in the films! The Tantive IV features an opening cockpit, rotating and elevating turbo laser cannons, rotating radar dish, removable roof section and interior command center. It also includes an opening compartment with removable cargo transport vehicle and 2 detachable escape pods for the droids to make their getaway with the Death Star plans! Includes Princess Leia, C-3PO, R2-D2, Captain Antilles and Rebel Trooper minifigures.Measures 20.5″ (52 cm) x 7.5″ (19 cm) x 5.5″ (14 cm). (From LEGO.com)

name: Volkswagen T1 Camper Van
description: For the gift with purchase "Mini" version, see set 40079-1.

name: Town Hall
description: Build the authentic 3-storey Town Hall! This highly detailed model features large entranceway columns, a coat of arms, a tall bell tower with clock and a large skylight that lets you see inside! On the ground floor, the large hall, tax office and auditorium have everything you need to run the town. Take the working elevator up to the secretary and mayor’s offices on the second floor, realistically furnished with desks, chairs, paintings and even a frog sculpture. Hold a meeting and address the town’s citizens at the podium! On the third floor, a spacious meeting room features a large conference table, chairs, globe and plants. Includes 8 minifigures: mayor, secretary, bride and groom, press woman, janitor and 2 children. Collect and build an entire town with the LEGO Modular Buildings collection: 10211-1 Grand Emporium, 10218-1 Pet Shop and 10197-1 Fire Brigade. Measures 10” (25.5cm) wide and 20” (50cm) high.(From LEGO.com)

name: Sopwith Camel
description: Recreate your very own piece of aviation history with the historic Sopwith Camel. This detailed replica of one of the most recognizable British single-seat biplanes ever to have graced the skies. Features include a realistic rotating propeller and engine cylinders, hinged tail rudder, realistic tension wires, functioning wing ailerons and tail flaps that can be controlled from the cockpit – just like the real plane! The detail doesn't stop there; this authentic model has over 880 bricks, including rare dark green, dark tan and metallic silver elements. Model measures over 15” (40cm) long and has a wingspan of over 19” (50cm).(From LEGO.com)For the "Mini" version, see set 40049-1.

name: B-wing Starfighter
description: Now you can experience the ultimate B-wing Starfighter from the Star Wars galaxy like never before. This fantastic model features everything you would expect from our premium collector range, including rotating, self-levelling cockpit and realistic wing configurations for landing and flight. And when you're finished battling in the skies above Endor or helping to restore freedom in the galaxy, place this highly detailed B-wing Starfighter on its own dedicated display stand and fact plaque. Measures 26” (66cm) wide and 15” (38cm) high in flight configuration, and 17” (43cm) high on display stand.(From LEGO.com)

name: Haunted House
description: The crooked Haunted House is home to the scariest ghosts and monsters. Tremble in fear as you open the gate, go weak at the knees as you step onto the porch and gasp in horror at the fireplace, kitchen, office, folding staircase, bedroom, potion room, music room and collection of other creepy objects. Dare you enter the Haunted House?! Measures 15.4” (39cm) high, 9.4” (24cm) wide and 7.5” (19cm) deep.(From LEGO.com)

name: Winter Village Cottage
description: Continuing the winter series, build the Winter Village Cottage for a perfect holiday home. Seat Grandpa snugly by the fireplace with his newspaper as you help Dad to put up the tree, then bake a feast in the kitchen with Mom! When it's time to stock up the storage shed with firewood, bring the kids for a ride with Dad on the sled watch him cut the wood with his chainsaw deep in the forest. When the snow gets really deep, clear the road with the snowplow, take all of the kids skiing or build an igloo to play in. There's no cozier place to spend long, frosty nights! Cottage measures 6.7” (17cm) high, 9.8” (25cm) wide and 5.5” (14cm) deep. Storage shed measures 4.3” (11cm) high, 2.7” (7cm) wide and 2.7” (7cm) deep. Igloo measures 2.7” (7cm) high, 2.7” (7cm) wide and 2.7” (7cm) deep. Snowplow measures 2.7” (7cm) high, 7” (18cm) long (with plow attached) and 2.3” (6cm) wide. Combine with other Winter Village items, like 10216-1 Winter Village Bakery or 10222-1 Winter Village Post Office!(From LEGO.com)

name: Mini Modulars
description: Available only to our LEGO VIP Program Members, this exclusive mini modulars set is an authentic miniature representation of the first 5 buildings in the Modular Building series: Café Corner, Market Street, Green Grocer, Fire Brigade and Grand Emporium. Featuring highly detailed design, each building can be displayed as a stand alone piece or connected to the others buildings in the set. The mini Café Corner includes details like a fan above the doorway and printed hotel signage, while the mini Market Street includes transparent bricks and a unique brick construction. The quaint mini Green Grocer also features transparent bricks and a fire escape at the rear, while the mini Fire Brigade includes a brick bell and white arch wall elements. Finally, the mini Grand Emporium has a rooftop sign, skylight and window washing platform. With fantastic detailing and a huge variety of elements in a range of rich colors, this exclusive mini modulars set is the perfect addition to every VIP Member's collection.(From LEGO.com)

name: MINI Cooper
description: This version was sold in a square box (rather than the later rectangular design) with original "Creator Expert" branding. This version included a front and rear windscreen element (part 2694) which many found poorly presented the iconic windscreens of the MINI Cooper Mark VII upon which this model is based. Reacting to these concerns, LEGO altered the building instructions in December 2014 and repositioned the two windscreens further into the body of the car. A more robust solution was found in mid-2015 with the creation of a new part (24607). This replacement part can be requested from LEGO Customer Service for those who own the initial version. Remember to add these replacement parts to your loose part inventory on Rebrickable since they are not included in this set's inventory!Beginning in July 2015, LEGO altered this set's packaging and included the more accurate windscreens in the box contents. For this late 2015 re-issue, see set 10242-2.For the gift-with-purchase "Mini Model" version, see set 40109-1.

name: MINI Cooper (Late 2015 Re-Issue)
description: This version was sold in a rectangular box (rather than the original square design) with newer "Creator Expert" branding. Additionally, the instructions and set contents were updated to include front and rear windscreens (part 24607) that are more accurate to the MINI Cooper Mark VII upon which the model is based.For the original 2014 version, see set 10242-1.For the gift-with-purchase "Mini Model" version, see set 40109-1.

name: Corner Garage
description: Drop by the LEGO Creator Expert 10264 Corner Garage, where you’ll discover a world of fun and surprises! This amazing model comes with removable building sections for easy access to the highly detailed interior and comprises 3 stories. On the ground level there’s a 1950s-style gas station with fuel pump, kiosk and a vehicle workshop complete with a roll-up door, vehicle lift and tire mounter. At the mid-level animal clinic you’ll find an examination table, fish tank, and a waiting area with sofa, while on the upper level you’ll discover a well-equipped apartment with kitchen, TV, sofa, bed and a staircase that leads to a rooftop terrace with sun lounger, parasol and flower garden. The exterior of the building features a classic 1950s facade with signage, detailed windows and a decorative roofline, plus a sidewalk area with a tree and an ornate streetlamp. This charming addition to the Modular Buildings series has been designed to provide a challenging and rewarding building experience, full of nostalgia. Also includes a scooter, tow truck and 6 minifigures, plus parrot, bunny, dog, frog and fish figures.Measures over 12” (32cm) high, 10” (26cm) wide and 9” (25cm) deep.Tow truck measures over 2” (6cm) high, 5” (14cm) long and 1” (5cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

All parts remain in the inventory as they all count towards the official part count.An alternatively colored, bright light blue version was released as part of the Fall 2021 LEGO product pilot as set 77942-1.

Inventory V1 reflects the earliest version, V2 reflects a later version of the set sold around April 2021.

name: Footshop x Adidas Originals Superstar 'Blueprinting' Bundle
description: Unnumbered limited edition bundle created to honor the sportswear retailer Footshop’s 10th anniversary.Includes an unmodified 10282-1 set and a customization kit to recreate the unique sole tread pattern and coloring of the 2020 Footshop x Adidas "Blueprinting" shoe collaboration.A total of 200 bundles were created for sale via Footshop's website and store locations in Prague (Czechia), Budapest (Hungary), Bucharest (Romania), and Bratislava (Slovakia).Florian Müller designed the stock set. Radovan Pekárek of the Czech LEGO Users Group, in collaboration with Footshop and LEGO, designed the customization kit. Building instructions for combining the two bundle components to create the modified model can be found here.

Open the yellow case to access multiple compartments where you can organize and store LEGO pieces. This set also includes simple, age-appropriate building instructions that will help children discover their own creative building skills. Suitcase measures over 10" (26cm) high, 11" (28cm) wide and 2" (6cm) deep.From LEGO.com.

name: Buzz and Bo Peep's Playground Adventure
Toy Story 4 RV Vacation
description: Help your child experience the adventure and fun of Disney•Pixar’s Toy Story 4 with the 10769 Toy Story 4 RV Vacation LEGO 4+ set! This jaunty set is developed to be fun and easy for preschoolers and youngsters, featuring a recreational vehicle (RV) with special Starter Brick chassis, removable roof and interior with bed, toilet and sink, plus a park building wall with special Starter Brick baseplate, tree, picnic table and a grill. The Starter Brick pieces help even first-time builders experience the pride of building vehicles, structures and more, all on their own. This great easy LEGO set also includes an RV Park sign with tree and opening gate. The included simple guide to build and play will help your young camper understand the purpose of the building steps and grow their imagination and confidence for the perfect start to LEGO model kits in an exciting new Toy Story 4 movie setting. Includes Jessie and Alien minifigures, plus Rex and Forky LEGO figures.(From Lego.com)

name: My First Tow Truck
description: Your child will love to rescue the broken-down car over and over again with LEGO DUPLO 10883 My First Tow Truck for toddlers. It’s easy to build and develops fine motor skills, while the toy tow truck and car have window bricks decorated with characters to encourage role-play. This compact little set is a great preschool toy to take and play wherever you go! DUPLO bricks are specially designed to be safe for little hands. Tow truck toy measures over 1” (7cm) high, 3” (12cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.Car measures over 2” (6cm) high, 3” (9cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: My First Balancing Animals
description: Toddlers will have loads of fun learning to build and balance with the LEGO DUPLO 10884 My First Balancing Animals! Have fun stacking the brightly colored jungle animals on the seesaw in lots of different ways and see how it makes this cute balancing toy tip! The colorful monkey, elephant, tiger and panda animals are easy to build and rebuild with chunky DUPLO bricks, and there are 2 extra bricks to help balance the seesaw or place underneath to hold it steady. DUPLO bricks are specially designed to be safe for little hands. Each animal measures over 2” (8cm) high, 2” (6cm) wide and 1” (3cm) deep.Seesaw balancing element measures over 1” (4cm) high, 7” (19cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: My First Fun Puzzle
description: The LEGO DUPLO 10885 My First Fun Puzzle toy for toddlers is an easy and entertaining start to matching, building and stacking blocks for very young children. Create and connect with your preschooler as you help them sort the bricks into colors and stack them in the right order to complete these easy-to-build favorite animal puzzles for kids. Then take them apart, mix them up and inspire imagination as you encourage them to come up with goofy animal creations of their own! The DUPLO bricks included with this fun block puzzle toddler toy are specially designed to be safe for little hands. Each animal measures over 4” (12cm) high, 2” (6cm) wide and 1” (3cm) deep.(From LEGO.com)

name: My First Car Creations
description: Preschoolers will love to build and rebuild colorful vehicles with LEGO DUPLO 10886 My First Car Creations. Help them sort the colors to build a toy helicopter, taxi, garbage truck and Fire Truck for toddlers, or mix up all the bricks and create endless easy-to-build car creations together by combining just a few chunky DUPLO bricks, developing fine motor skills as you go. This toddler toy car set is great for developing imagination as preschoolers learn to create and move with classic car play. DUPLO bricks are specially designed to be fun and safe for small hands. Fire truck measures over 4” (11cm) high, 3” (9cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.Helicopter measures over 3” (9cm) high, 3” (9cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.Taxi measures over 2” (6cm) high, 3” (9cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.Garbage truck measures over 2” (7cm) high, 3” (10cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Creative Fun
description: Young children will love to build a rainbow of colorful models with the LEGO DUPLO 10887 Creative Fun building set, developing fine motor and cognitive skills as they go. With 120 classic DUPLO building bricks in bright colors, this set is the perfect preschool toy to inspire creativity for kids, allowing you to connect with them through free-building fun. This great building set includes ideas for easy-to-build toy parrots, a castle, balloons, an apple and a boat—after that the sky's the limit! DUPLO bricks are specially designed to be fun and safe for small hands. (From LEGO.com)

name: Spider-Man vs. Electro
description: Little superheroes will enjoy using their imaginations for hours of role-play fun with this LEGO DUPLO 10893 Spider-Man vs Electro construction toy. Help Marvel’s Spider-Man sling his web to stop Electro from robbing the bank and gather his evidence with the toy camera! Create and connect with your preschooler and develop their fine motor skills as they build and rebuild the bank vault with opening toy safe. This Spider-Man toy building set includes 2 LEGO DUPLO figures: Spider-Man and Electro. Bank with safe measures over 5” (14cm) high, 7” (19cm) wide and 2” (6cm) deep.(From LEGO.com)

name: Emmet and Lucy's Visitors from the DUPLO Planet
description: Introduce your toddler to the color and creativity of THE LEGO MOVIE 2 with this LEGO DUPLO 10895 Emmet and Lucy’s Visitors from the DUPLO Planet preschool toy. Little fans of Emmet and Lucy will love helping them defend against the easy-to-build alien invaders! Then mix all the bright and chunky DUPLO bricks up so young children can create more aliens of their own, developing imagination and fine motor skills on their journey to becoming the next master builder! Includes 2 LEGO DUPLO figures: Emmet and Lucy, plus 4 buildable alien invaders. Largest alien invader measures over 9” (25cm) high, 5” (13cm) wide and 2” (6cm) deep.Alien invader with slide measures over 6” (17cm) high, 2” (6cm) wide and 5” (13cm) deep.(From LEGO.com)

Create animals, buildings, vehicles and LEGO models with a hint of nostalgia, including an old-fashioned typewriter and a vintage biplane. This set offers 3 levels of building complexity and makes an excellent starter set for budding LEGO builders. Includes age-appropriate building instructions to help children unlock their creative building skills, with further inspiration available online.(From LEGO.com)

name: Löwenstein Castle
description: Available for purchase during the 2019 BrickLink AFOL Designer Program, a collaboration between BrickLink and LEGO in honor of the 60th anniversary of the LEGO brick. While this program's sets were not considered "official" LEGO sets at the time of their release, in light of the official continuation of the program in 2021 as the BrickLink Designer Program, Rebrickable has decided to include these sets in the database.Limited edition of 2500 individually numbered sets with the numbered box sleeve doubling as a photographic backdrop.Pre-orders for this set were planned for acceptance between February 1 and April 15, 2019 including free global shipping and normal purchases (including shipping charges) were planned for between April 16 and June 30, 2019. However, due to high interest, this set sold out prior to the end of the pre-order phase (exact date unknown but believed to be in early April 2019) and no orders were accepted during the normal purchase window.

name: Antique Fire Engine
description: Available for purchase during the 2019 BrickLink AFOL Designer Program, a collaboration between BrickLink and LEGO in honor of the 60th anniversary of the LEGO brick. While this program's sets were not considered "official" LEGO sets at the time of their release, in light of the official continuation of the program in 2021 as the BrickLink Designer Program, Rebrickable has decided to include these sets in the database. Limited edition of no more than 2500 individually numbered sets with the numbered box sleeve doubling as a photographic backdrop. Pre-orders for this set were accepted between February 1 and April 15, 2019 including free global shipping. Normal purchases (including shipping charges) were accepted between April 16 and June 30, 2019.Additionally, ten sets (unsold from the original allotment) were made available as potential prizes for completing a survey about BrickLink between March 27 and April 7, 2021.

While this program's sets were not considered "official" LEGO sets at the time of their release, in light of the official continuation of the program in 2021 as the BrickLink Designer Program, Rebrickable has decided to include these sets in the database.Limited edition of no more than 2500 individually numbered sets with the numbered box sleeve doubling as a photographic backdrop. Pre-orders for this set were accepted between February 1 and April 15, 2019 including free global shipping. Normal purchases (including shipping charges) were accepted between April 16 and June 30, 2019.

name: Building My SG - Reflect, Celebrate, Inspire
description: Presented as a free gift from the Singapore Ministry of Education to all primary school students and teachers in honor of the 50th anniversary of Singapore's independence in May 2015. This version of the set was never available for retail purchase.The set includes instructions for building three different difficult levels of various iconic Singapore landmarks. The various landmarks cannot be built simultaneously from the provided parts. The landmarks represented are:* Cavenagh Bridge* Changi Airport* Gardens by the BayFor the identical set, except for alternative packaging, that was available for sale to the general public, see set 2000446-2

name: Building My SG - Reflect, Celebrate, Inspire (Special Commemorative Edition)
description: Available for purchase by the general public in limited quantities for S$50 from the Singapore Ministry of Education in honor of the 50th anniversary of Singapore's independence in May 2015. This version of the set has a sticker applied to the box reading "Special Commemorative Edition" and including the "SG50" logo. This sticker covers the original message announcing that the set was a gift from the Ministry of Education to Singapore's youth.The set includes instructions for building three different difficult levels of various iconic Singapore landmarks. The various landmarks cannot be built simultaneously from the provided parts. The landmarks represented are:* Cavenagh Bridge* Changi Airport* Gardens by the BayFor the version that was presented as a free gift to primary schoolchildren, see set 2000446-1.

name: Discover More
description: Designed as take-home, parent engagement component of the FIRST LEGO League Discover program (formerly known as the FIRST LEGO League Jr. Discovery Edition program).Includes two sets of the "Six Bricks" which form a core component of the program.Unlike Set 2000460-1 which contained the identical inventory, this set's packaging does not reflect any specific season of the program allowing for its use over multiple years.

name: Big Ben
description: For the larger scale Creator Expert version, see set 10253-1Big Ben is also depicted in LEGO form in two additional sets from the Disney Pixar CARS franchise - sets 5828-1 (DUPLO scale) and 8639-1 (System scale).Additionally, Big Ben is amongst the landmarks depicted on the 21034-1 London Architecture Skyline set and the 40569-1 London Postcard Creator set. This is the first set in the Architecture theme to be designed by someone other than Adam Reed Tucker.

name: Villa Savoye
description: Based on the house in the Paris suburb of Poissy, France

name: Sungnyemun
description: Available exclusively for purchase at the Danish Pavilion of EXPO 2012 between May 12 and May 31, 2012 (with sales continuing there until the end of EXPO 2012 on August 12, 2012). Made available for wider retail purchase beginning on June 1, 2012 from LEGO Brand Retail, LEGOLAND Stores and the LEGO Shop website.Early information about this set led many to anticipated it would be named "Namdaemun Gate" - a popular alternative name for the same site. The final name is the one officially recognized by the South Korean government.N.B.: Despite officially being part of the Landmark Series (and being depicted as such in multiple building instruction manuals), the non-North American version of the packaging for this set incorrectly assigns this set to the Architect Series. The North American packaging correctly reflects this as being in the Landmark Series.

name: The Eiffel Tower
description: This is the first set in the Architecture theme to have two identified designers. The designer's names do not appear on the set packaging (also a first for the theme). Additionally, this is the first set in the Architecture theme to exclude an "A Word from the Artist" statement in the building instructions.Tiles presenting the name of this set in English ("The Eiffel Tower") and French ("La tour Eiffel") are both included in the set. Select the appropriate inventory for the version in your collection.For the larger scale Creator Expert version, see set 10181-1.The Eiffel Tower is also amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21044-1 Paris Architecture Skyline set.

name: Small Store Set
description: There are many alternatives for this set, listing different Brick 1 x 6 and with print. Since it's unclear in what combinations these bricks came, we've created a dummy set for them: 210-2-DUMMY-1.

name: Marina Bay Sands
description: Limited edition release of 10,000 sets (and identified as a "Limited Edition" on the set's packaging).Available for purchase from Singapore Toys R Us locations, "LEGO Mono Brand Stores" (limited-time pop-up stores in Singapore) and the hotel gift shop of the Marina Bay Sands. Additionally, a limited number of sets were sold via the LEGO Shop website in South Korea.Marina Bay Sands is amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21057-1 Singapore Architecture Skyline set.See our review of this set!

name: Lincoln Memorial
description: While Rok Zgalin Kobe is confirmed as the designer of this set, his name does not appear on the packaging nor is an artist statement included in the building instructions.Designed to match the scale of the 21030-1 United States Capitol Building. A micro-scale version was created as a promotional set for The LEGO Americana Roadshow.

name: Flatiron Building
description: While Rok Zgalin Kobe is confirmed as the set designer, his name does not appear on the packaging nor is an artist statement included in the building instructions.The Flatiron Building is amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21028-1 New York City Architecture Skyline set.

name: Louvre

name: New York City

The Empire State Building is the sole focus of two other sets (21002-1 and 21046-1) in the Architecture theme. The Flatiron Building is the sole focus of another set (21023-1) in the Architecture theme.

name: Dummy Set for 210-2
description: Dummy Set for all possible prints of 3009/3009a found in set 210-2.

name: United States Capitol Building
description: Designed to match the scale of the 21022-1 Lincoln Memorial.A micro-scale version was created as a promotional set for The LEGO Americana Roadshow.

name: Burj Khalifa
description: This is the first landmark to be depicted for a second time in an Architecture theme set as the sole focus.Burj Khalifa is amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21052-1 Dubai Architecture Skyline setFor the 2011 version, see set 21008-1Re-issued in 2019 as set 21055-1 with updated packaging and building instructions, including Arabic in both, for sale in the Middle East

name: Sydney
description: Depicts the following landmarks:* Sydney Tower* Deutsche Bank Place* Sydney Opera House* Sydney Harbour BridgeSydney Opera House is the sole focus of another set (21012-1) in the Architecture theme and a larger scale Creator Expert set (10234-1)

name: Chicago
description: Depicts the following landmarks:* Big Red* Willis Tower* Cloud Gate* DuSable Bridge* The Wrigley Building* John Hancock CenterWillis Tower is the sole focus of another set (21000-2) in the Architecture theme.The same structure, under the former name "Sears Tower", is the sole focus of two sets in the Architecture theme - a limited edition Brickstructures version (19710-1) and a general release version (21000-1).John Hancock Center is the sole focus of two sets in the Architecture theme - a limited edition Brickstructures version (19720-1) and a general release version (21001-1).

name: London
description: Depicts the following landmarks:* The National Gallery* Nelson's Column* Big Ben* London Eye* Tower BridgeThe National Gallery and Nelson's Column are both located on Trafalgar Square - the focus of another set (21045-1) in the Architecture theme.Big Ben is the sole focus of another set (21013-1) in the Architecture theme and a larger scale Creator Expert set (10253-1). Big Ben is also depicted in animated form as "Big Bentley" in two additional sets from the Disney Pixar CARS franchise - sets 5828-1 (DUPLO scale) and 8639-1 (System scale). Additionally, Big Ben and the London Eye both appear amongst the landmarks depicted on the 40569-1 London Postcard Creator set. Tower Bridge is the sole focus of a larger scale Creator Expert set (10214-1).Available exclusively for purchase at the LEGO Store Leicester Square in London, United Kingdom between November 16 and December 31, 2016 (with sales continuing there afterwards) in honor of the grand opening of this new "flagship" store. Made available for wider retail purchase beginning on January 1, 2017, including at LEGO Stores and the LEGO Shop website.

name: Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum
description: For the 2009 "Architect Series" version, see set 21004-1.N.B.: The Architecture theme stopped designating sets to a specific "series" in 2016. Therefore, unlike the previous version of the Guggenheim Museum, this version is considered a portion of the theme's primary range.

name: Arc de Triomphe
description: Arc de Triomphe is amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21044-1 Paris Architecture Skyline set and the 40568-1 Paris Postcard Creator set

name: LEGO House

name: Las Vegas

In the redesign, the Mandalay Bay Resort was replaced by the Bellagio Hotel.An extremely limited number (approximately 24) of these sets were sold by retailers in South Africa. For more information, see the article by the Brick Architect found here

name: Trafalgar Square
description: This set was launched at a designer set signing event held at the LEGO Store in Leicester Square (London, United Kingdom) on April 27, 2019. Approximately 500 sets were signed during this event.Available exclusively for purchase at the LEGO Store Leicester Square in London, United Kingdom between April 27 and June 1, 2019 (with sales continuing there afterwards). Made available for wider European retail purchase beginning on June 1, 2019, including at LEGO Stores and the LEGO Shop website. Made available for worldwide retail purchase beginning on August 1, 2019.The National Gallery and Nelson's Column are both located on Trafalgar Square. These are amongst the landmarks depicted on the 21034-1 London Architecture Skyline set.

name: Empire State Building
description: For the 2009 version, see set 21002-1.The Empire State Building is also amongst the landmarks depicted in the 21028-1 New York City Architecture Skyline set.

name: Las Vegas

The Mandalay Bay Resort was replaced by the Bellagio Hotel.

name: Architecture Studio
description: Designed in collaboration with leading architects to help people learn the fundamentals of architectural design.Includes an inspirational guidebook filled with 272 pages of tips, techniques, features, and intuitive hands-on exercises endorsed by REX architecture, Sou Fujimoto Architects, Skidmore Owings & Merrill LLP (SOM), MAD Architects, Tham & Videgård Arkitekter and Safdie Architects.Available exclusively at a number of events hosted by local architects and held at Barnes & Noble locations in the United States in July 2013. Made available for wider retail purchase in the United States beginning on August 1, 2013, including at LEGO Stores and the LEGO Shop website. Re-launched for Europe at an event held at LEGO Store Westfield (Shepherd’s Bush) in London, United Kingdom on July 31, 2014 with wider retail availability throughout Europe beginning on August 1, 2014.

name: Tokyo

description: Ideas range #011Build an authentic replica of the iconic TARDIS time machine in LEGO bricks! Features an opening TARDIS, detachable interior console room with assorted flight controls, exclusive graphic details and steps. Great for display or role-playing scenes from the TV series. Includes 4 minifigures with assorted accessory elements: the Eleventh Doctor, the Twelfth Doctor, Clara Oswald and a Weeping Angel, plus 2 Daleks. Includes a booklet about the fan-designer and the BBC television series. The perfect gift for LEGO and Doctor Who fans of all ages!TARDIS measures over 4” (11cm) high, 2” (6cm) wide and 2” (6cm) deep. Console room measures over 5” (14cm) high, 6” (16cm) wide and 8” (21cm) deep. name: 2 x 8 Bricks  (EUR/UK/AUS)
description: This set was released in Europe in 1958 (AT/BE/NL/PT/CH/IT) and 1959 (FR/FI); in Britain and Ireland in 1960, and in Australia in 1962. It was not released as a set in Denmark, where individual 2 x 8 bricks were still being sold as 700/16. By 1958 Denmark switched to the 215 set number, but still for single bricks. (Retailers Refill box 215-5 -not yet available- contained 25 bricks). Individual Danish parts sales ended in 1965.This set replaced the 1956 version (215-4) that contained hollow Mursten bricks, and it contained six 2 x 8 tubed bricks in a single color. There were four different colors available: blue (215-2B), red (215-2R), white (215-2W) and yellow (215-2Y).The set was also released by Samsonite in the United States (USA) and Canada (CAN) as set 215-3, but this set was also available in black, a color that was not available in Europe.The 215 bricks spare pack was discontinued in 1966 (EU/GB). In 1977, set number 215 was re-used for set 215-1 - Red Indians.The catalog entries (below) show set 215-2 in a 1959 German catalog (left) and a 1961 British catalog (right).

name: 2 x 8 Bricks (USA/CAN)
description: This set was released by Samsonite in the United States in 1961 and in Canada in 1962. In the USA it contained nine 2 x 8 tubed bricks in a single color. There were four different colors available: blue (215-3B), red (215-3R), white (215-3W) and yellow (215-3Y). In 1962/1963 Samsonite added a black (215-3Bk) version. The Canadian version contained only eight bricks, in blue, red, white, yellow and black.The set was also released in Europe, Britain and Australia as set 215-2, but not in black.The 215 bricks spare pack was discontinued in 1965 (CAN) and 1966 (USA). In 1977, set number 215 was re-used for set 215-1 - Red Indians.The catalog entries (below) show set 215-3 in a 1963 American catalog (left) and a 1963 Canadian catalog (right).

This 3-in-1 LEGO Creator set features a three-part modular design that enables quick model reconfiguration, and can be combined with the 31055-1 and 31060-1 LEGO Creator mini modular vehicle sets to create new vehicles for extended play. Rebuild to create a 31054-1-b1 - Fast Train or a 31054-1-b2 - Carriage.Blue Express measures over 1" (4cm) high, 3" (9cm) long and 1" (4cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

This 3-in-1 LEGO Creator set features a three-part modular design that enables quick model reconfiguration, and can be combined with the 31054-1 and 31060-1 LEGO Creator mini modular vehicle sets to create new vehicles for extended play. Rebuild to create a 31055-1-b1 - Tow Truck or a 31055-1-b2 - Race Car.Red Racer measures over 1" (3cm) high, 3" (8cm) long and 1" (3cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

description: Drive in style with this sleek open-top Green Cruiser, featuring a green, white and black color scheme, tinted windshield, opening front trunk and rear hood, detailed engine, and a large two-minifigure cockpit with detailed dashboard and steering wheel. The 3-in-1 LEGO Creator model has a three-part modular design for quick model reconfiguration, and rebuilds into a Fast Boat or a Truck.Green Cruiser measures over 1" (3cm) high, 4" (12cm) long and 2" (6cm) wide.Fast Boat measures over 1" (3cm) high, 4" (12cm) long and 2" (6cm) wide.Truck measures over 2" (6cm) high, 3" (10cm) long and 2" (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Air Blazer
description: Complete secret missions with the agile, high-speed Air Blazer helicopter, featuring spinning main rotor and tail rotor, tinted cockpit, large engines, rear landing light and a red and black color scheme. This 3-in-1 LEGO Creator model rebuilds into a 31057-1-b1 - Seaplane or a 31057-1-b2 - Catamaran.Air Blazer measures over 1" (5cm) high, 8" (21cm) long and 6" (16cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Island Adventures
description: Head for exciting destinations aboard the huge seaplane, featuring a bright-yellow, white and dark-blue color scheme, twin engines with spinning propellers, twin booms, adjustable elevator, landing floats, and an opening cargo hatch and cockpit with detailed dashboard. Also includes a tropical island with two palm trees, plus an empty bottle and a map. Rebuild this 3-in-1 LEGO Creator model into an Island Hut or a Speedboat. Includes a minifigure.Seaplane measures over 3" (8cm) high, 9" (24cm) long and 11" (29cm) wide.Island measures over 2" (6cm) high, 2" (7cm) wide and 2" (6cm) deep.Island Hut measures over 6" (17cm) high, 6" (16cm) wide and 5" (13cm) deep.Speedboat measures over 3" (9cm) high, 6" (17cm) long and 3" (8cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

LEGO Customer Service can provide the missing parts upon request.

name: Futuristic Flyer
description: Get set for supersonic fun with the LEGO Creator 3in1 31086 Futuristic Flyer, featuring an awesome dark red and white color scheme, forward swept wings, tinted cockpit, fixed landing gear and a flaming jet engine. With this LEGO Creator 3in1 set you get 3 different build and play experiences. Build the Futuristic Flyer and then rebuild it into a Futuristic Spaceship toy or a Futuristic LEGO Robot with wings and backpack for more sci-fi fun.From: LEGO.com.

name: Deep Sea Creatures
description: Enjoy sea life adventures with the LEGO Creator 3in1 31088 Deep Sea Creatures set, featuring a scary shark toy with a realistic dark-blue and white color scheme, opening mouth full of pointy teeth, moving fins, movable body joints and reflective eyes, plus a posable crab with a box of treasure. With LEGO Creator 3in1 play sets you get 3 different build and play experiences. Build the Shark and crab toys, and then rebuild them to create a posable Squid or a wide-mouthed Angler Fish for even more deep sea fun. (From LEGO.com)

Bring nature indoors

description: This set was re-designed during its production life to include 26 Red 3020 plates to provide additional stability to the field. Versions of the set including either Red or Yellow 6019 clips are known to exist in both design versions. Be sure to select the correct inventory for the set in your collection!A special release of this set, including additional minifigures in Orange jerseys to represent the Dutch National Team, was released exclusively in Europe (perhaps exclusively in only select countries in Europe) and can be found as set 3409-2. Unconfirmed reports also exist of another special release of this set, including either additional minifigures or stickers sheets to represent the English National Team, being released in the United Kingdom (perhaps as a Woolworths exclusive). If you can provide further information on this variant (especially photos), please submit a Change Request.

name: The LEGOLAND Train (LEGO Inside Tour Version)
description: Available exclusively as a gift for attendees of the LEGO Inside Tour during sessions in 2014. Exact production numbers are unknown but likely around 160 (including 130 tour participants and additional sets for internal LEGO use). The sets are hand-numbered out of 80 but it has been confirmed that numbering was on a per-Inside Tour session basis.For the LEGO Fan Weekend Skaerbaek version, see set 4000014-2.For the hand-numbered, LEGOLAND Florida Ambassador passholder version, see set 4000014-3.N.B.: Two 91988 Light Bluish Gray 2x14 Plates are included in the box's part count but are not needed to complete the model build. These parts have been listed as spare parts in the Rebrickable inventory.

name: The LEGOLAND Train (LEGO Fan Weekend Skaerbaek Version)
description: Available exclusively as a gift to participating exhibitors at the LEGO Fan Weekend Skaerbaek held at LEGOLAND Billund in 2014. While unnumbered, approximately 350 sets were produced.For the LEGO Inside Tour version, see set 4000014-1.For the LEGOLAND Florida Ambassador passholder version, see set 4000014-3.N.B.: Two 91988 Light Bluish Gray 2x14 Plates are included in the box's part count but are not needed to complete the model build. These parts have been listed as spare parts in the Rebrickable inventory.

name: The LEGOLAND Train (LEGOLAND Ambassador Pass Version)
description: Available exclusively as a gift to Ambassador Passholders at LEGOLAND Florida. This set was limited to active passholders for the 2014 season only and is hand-numbered out of a production run of 62. Despite being released only at LEGOLAND Florida, the stickers identify LEGOLAND Billund (the home of the modeled train).For the hand-numbered, LEGO Inside Tour version, see set 4000014-1.For the LEGO Fan Weekend Skaerbaek version, see set 4000014-2.N.B.: Two 91988 Light Bluish Gray 2x14 Plates are included in the box's part count but are not needed to complete the model build. These parts have been listed as spare parts in the Rebrickable inventory.

name: LEGO House Tree of Creativity
description: Available exclusively as a gift for attendees of a LEGO Inside Tour during 2017. This set was never available for retail purchase.Based on the "Tree of Creativity" located within the LEGO House in Billund, Denmark. Sets are individually numbered out of 80 with sets 1-35 reserved for Inside Tour attendees and the remainder distributed to LEGO personnel involved with that particular tour. The numbering system is reused for each Inside Tour. The reverse of each tour's packaging includes a photo of that tour's attendees. Based on there being five tours in 2017, this set is limited to a total of 400 sets (80 in each packaging sleeve).For the "Nonnie" BrickHeadz also presented as a gift to attendees of these tours, see set ITBH-1.A second, slightly smaller variation of the "Tree of Creativity" with a production run of 10,000 sets and including fewer minifigures and fewer minibuilds on the tree was released exclusively at the LEGO House in Billund, Denmark in 2018 as set 4000026-1.

name: Ferguson Tractor
description: Available exclusively as a gift for attendees of a LEGO Inside Tour during 2018. This set was never available for retail purchase.Based on a 1950's-era tractor which was recreated as a cast metal toy in the early days of the LEGO company.Sets are individually numbered out of 80 with sets 1-35 reserved for Inside Tour attendees and the remainder distributed to LEGO personnel involved with that particular tour. The numbering system is reused for each Inside Tour. The reverse of each tour's packaging includes a photo of that tour's attendees. Based on there being five tours in 2018, this set is limited to a total of 400 sets (80 in each packaging sleeve).

name: Tree of Creativity
description: Available exclusively from LEGO Store located in the LEGO House in Billund, Denmark and based on the structure at the same location.Production run limited to 10,000 sets.The "Tree of Creativity" was also the focus of a set (4000024-1) presented as a gift to attendees of the 2017 LEGO Inside Tour. That version is slightly larger and includes more minifigures and minibuilds on the tree.

name: Exclusive T. Rex
description: Designed for use in various promotional competitions from various vendors worldwide.While the sets are unnumbered, the global distribution was reportedly limited to 500 sets.Known competitions and available quantities are:* May 2018 - Dreamland  in Belgium - 100 copies* June 2018 - Smyths in United Kingdom - 10 copies* June/July 2018 - Toys R Us in France - 53 copies* July/August 2018 - Toys R Us in Singapore - 16 copies* July/August 2018 - LEGO Certified Store in Pavilion KL, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia - 16 copies

name: The LEGO System House
description: Available exclusively as a gift for attendees of the LEGO Inside Tour during sessions in 2019. Based on an actual LEGO company structure in Billund, Denmark now known as the "LEGO Idea House". Additional information on the building and the opening event depicted can be found here. This set includes the first LEGO part ever produced for an official set through 3D printing. An alternative build using five injection moulded plastic parts is also presented in the building instructions.

name: The Playful 5 Minifigure Set
description: Provided as a gift to LEGO employees participating in corporate Play Day events held on September 6, 2019 at various LEGO facilities around the world.The QR code is a link to a specially created Play Everyday mobile website.

name: LEGO Factory AGV
description: Available exclusively as a gift for attendees of a LEGO Inside Tour during 2022. This set was never available for retail purchase.Based on Automated Guided Vehicles found in LEGO factories around the world. This design is specifically based on AGVs operating in the Kornmarken moulding factory in Billund, Denmark which were observed by Inside Tour participants. Sets are individually numbered out of 80 with sets 1-35 reserved for Inside Tour attendees and the remainder distributed to LEGO personnel involved with that particular tour. The numbering system is reused for each Inside Tour. The reverse of each tour's packaging includes a photo of that tour's attendees. Based on there being four tours in 2022 (May 18-20, June 1-3, August 31-September 2 and September 14-16), this set is limited to a total of 320 sets (80 in each packaging sleeve).N.B.: No Inside Tours were conducted in 2020 or 2021 due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

name: Personalised Mosaic Portrait
description:
Available for sale at select LEGO Brand Stores and LEGO Certified Stores which have a LEGO Mosaic Maker photo booth including:
Beijing (Wangfujing), China
Hangzho (Westlake), China
Shanghai (People's Square), China
Billund (LEGO House), Denmark
Paris (Les Halles), France
Berlin, Germany
Yokohama (Landmark Plaza), Japan
Amsterdam, The Netherlands
Sentosa Gateway, Singapore
London (Leicester Square), United Kingdom
Anaheim (Downtown Disney District), California, United States
New York City (Flatiron District), New York, United States
Additionally, this set was available for sale at the following locations:
LEGOLAND Windsor Resort Hotel, United Kingdom
Toys R Us in Ocean Terminal, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong (limited time pop-up from January to July 2018)
Beginning in January 2021 (United States) and February 2021 (United Kingdom), this set was available for purchase from the online LEGO Shop. Early, erroneous images and text on the online LEGO Shop indicated the set would be expanded in size. LEGO Customer Service has confirmed this error and indicated the in-person and online purchased sets are the same and both of the same part count.While building instructions are customized based on either the in-person photo taken in the Mosaic Maker booth or via an online design tool, the set contents are always the same. For in-person purchases, a printout of the instructions is provided. For online purchases, customers are directed to save digital copies of their instructions prior to concluding their use of the online design tool. The set is packaged into five separate boxes (one per color of 1x1 plate) along with the baseplate and brick separator inside the set packaging.

name: LEGO House Dinosaurs
description: Based on the models displayed in the LEGO House in Billund, Denmark with the three dinosaurs representing the DUPLO, System and Technic design systems. Initially, available exclusively for on-site purchase at the LEGO Shop within the LEGO House in Billund, Denmark. Between May and June 2020, this set was available via online ordering restricted to Denmark, Ireland and the United Kingdom as a result of COVID-19 pandemic lockdown restrictions. The limited sales locations resulted from the set’s packaging containing only that information required for sales in Denmark but failing to contain information needed for a wider distribution. This offering was stopped once LEGO House reopened under adjusted COVID guidelines. Beginning in October 2022, the set was made available for online ordering once again via the online LEGO Shop but remained restricted to Denmark, Ireland and the United Kingdom.

name: London Postcard
description:
Depicts the following landmarks:
Big Ben
Piccadilly Circus
London Eye
A London Routemaster Bus
Big Ben is the sole focus of set 21013-1 in the Architecture theme and a larger scale Creator Expert set (10253-1). Big Ben is also depicted in animated form as "Big Bentley" in two additional sets from the Disney Pixar CARS franchise - sets 5828-1 (DUPLO scale) and 8639-1 (System scale).Both Big Ben and the London Eye appear in the 21034-1 London Architecture Skyline set.

A portion of these sets were withheld for internal distribution by the LEGO Group, DC Comics and the event organizers.Packaged in upgraded, hard cardboard slipcase sealed with the set's unique edition number.The parts for Batman are packed in a bag labeled 6182254. The parts for The Joker are packed in a bag labeled 6182255.

The difference is that both a plain white 87079 and the set-exclusive license plate are included in the set. Since only one of these two parts is used in the actual build, Rebrickable stores the plain version in the spare parts inventory.

name: Coding Express
description: From the LEGO Education description:"This intuitive solution brings students all aboard to learn the basic language of the digital age in a creative way. Coding Express combines digital and physical elements like action bricks and switches to introduce early learning students to coding concepts like sequencing, looping, and conditional coding. Students will learn collaboration, language, critical thinking skills, and more as they explore and create play scenarios using a classic train set."Teacher Guides and Lesson Plans are available digitally here.Digital copies of the 6 double-sided building inspiration cards can be found here.

name: Letters
description: "Featuring English letters in a rainbow of colors, the included inspiration cards and Getting Started activities help children learn the alphabet, recognize and write letters, identify phonemes and spell short words and names.Building plates, small trucks and doors also inspire children to match upper and lowercase letters, create compound words, group vowels and consonants, and play fun activities like guess the missing letter."(from LEGO Education website)

name: Animals
description: "Includes 4 double-sided building inspiration cards depicting 8 different habitats to help children learn what animals need to survive and how they differ. A Getting Started card with 5 activity ideas is also included to promote children's 21st century skills, like social and emotional development and early math skills in a safe and playful learning environment."(From LEGO Education website)

name: Metroliner
description: Marketed in Europe as "Euro Express"Re-issued as part of the LEGO Legends series in 2001 as set 10001-1.Can be expanded with Club Car (set 4547-1), itself re-issued as set 10002-1.Can be motorized using the 4548-1: Transformer and Speed Regulator or similar parts from other sets."This set came with a choice of two modern styled locomotives, either of which could be constructed using the various pieces in the box. The model shown here contained a combined driver's cabin and dining car area separated by an engine space. The train ran on metal tracks and the set also contained a buildable railway platform and 11 minifigures. Originally from 1991, this model was one of the few sets to be relaunched with completely new packaging as part of the LEGO Legends series in 2001."-- From employee gift re-creation (set 4002016-1-s4) building instructions.

name: Large Hub
description: Description from LEGO Education site:"The LEGO® Technic™ Large Hub is an advanced yet simple-to-use brick-shaped device featuring 6 input/output ports for connecting a variety of sensors and motors, a customizable 5x5 light matrix, Bluetooth connectivity, speaker, 6-axis gyro, rechargeable lithium-ion battery and a micro USB port for connectivity with compatible computers and tablets. The Large Hub can also be built together with LEGO Technic and System elements to create fun robots, dynamic devices and other interactive models."

name: Large Angular Motor
description: "The LEGO® Technic™ Large Angular Motor is the ideal solution for high-power, high-torque applications, featuring an integrated rotation sensor and absolute positioning for true straight-line control."

name: Medium Angular Motor
description: Description from LEGO Education site:"Build high-response robots with the LEGO® Technic™ Medium Angular Motor featuring low-profile design, integrated rotation sensor with absolute positioning and 1-degree accuracy.• Ideal for lower-load, fast-response applications. • Low-profile design for smaller models where space is limited. • Absolute positioning and integrated rotation sensor for true straight-line control. • Tacho feedback control for 1° accuracy. • Zero-point markings for simple calibration. • Simple form factor for quick building and rebuilding."

name: Distance Sensor
description: Description from LEGO Education site:"Deliver high-accuracy results with the LEGO® Technic™ Distance Sensor, featuring 1-200cm range, +/- 1cm accuracy, programmable LED ‘eyes’ and an integrated 6-pin adaptor for third-party sensors, boards and DIY hardware.• Sound wave sensor features 1-200cm range with +/- 1cm accuracy for accurate, repeatable results. • Programmable LED ‘eyes’ add life to any build. • Integrated industry-standard interface for third-party sensors, boards and DIY hardware. • Simple form factor for quick building and rebuilding."

name: Color Sensor
description: Description from LEGO Education site: "The LEGO® Technic™ Color Sensor detects colors and measures reflected and ambient light from darkness to bright sunlight.• High-accuracy 1kHz sample rate delivers consistent, accurate data for repeatable results. • Detects colors. • Measures intensity of reflected white light and ambient light. • Simple form factor for quick building and rebuilding."

name: Force Sensor
description: Description from LEGO Education site:"The LEGO® Technic™ Force Sensor measures pressures of up to 10 Newtons (~1kg) for accurate, repeatable results. The sensor can also be used as a touch sensor when pressed, released or bumped.• Measures up to 10 Newtons (~1kg). • Doubles as a touch sensor with pressed/released/bumped detection. • Simple form factor for quick building and rebuilding."

name: Small Angular Motor
description: Features a compact design profile and an integrated rotation sensor with absolute positioning and precise accuracy.• Ideal for low-load applications.• Compact design profile – great when space is at a premium.• Absolute positioning and integrated rotation sensor.• Magnet feedback control for precise accuracy.• Zero-point markings for simple calibration.• Simple form factor for quick building and rebuilding.• For use with the Small Hub (45609-1) or Large Hub (45601-1)— LEGO Education websiteEID for part is 6305270

name: 3×3 Color Light Matrix
description: From LEGO Education website:• 9 programmable pixels each display up to 10 colors and 10 brightness levels for endless creativity• For use with the Small Hub (45609-1) and Large Hub (45601-1)EID for part is 6275773

name: Small Hub

This high-capacity, 2,000 mAh battery can be charged while fitted to the hub using a micro USB cable and can also be removed quickly and conveniently without the need for tools.• High-capacity 2,000 mAh lithium-ion battery for extended use between charges.• In-situ charging via USB cable.• Quick, tool-free battery replacement.

name: World Robotic Olympiad Brick Set
description: The WRO Brick Set is an assortment of bricks intended for use in any WRO Regular Category challenge – independent of age group.The bricks in one box are enough to construct all LEGO objects for one Regular Category challenge. In other words, one WRO Bricks set is good for one game table in either Elementary, Junior High or High School.The WRO Brick Set can be reused for future seasons, no change in the assortment of bricks is envisaged for next 3-4 seasons.The WRO Brick Set comes with no building instructions. All instructions to build these objects are given in the game rules for the respective Regular Category.

name: BOOMTOWN BUILD Discovery Set
description: Created for use in the FIRST LEGO League Jr. Discovery Edition program during the 2019-2020 "BOOMTOWN BUILD" season.This set was used to launch FLL Jr. Discovery Edition programs on a global basis.Includes parts needed to construct the Discovery Model along with five sets of the program's core "Six Bricks" component.

name: RePLAY Challenge Kit
description: Created for use during 2020-2021 FIRST LEGO League Challenge "RePLAY" season. This set rebranded the FIRST LEGO League’s senior division previously without a formal name into "FIRST LEGO League Challenge" on a worldwide basis. Packaged in a cardboard box containing the challenge mat and a large number of part bags.

name: PLAYMAKERS Explore Set
description: Created for use during the 2020-2021 FIRST LEGO League Explore "PLAYMAKERS" season.This set rebranded "FIRST LEGO League Jr." into "FIRST LEGO League Explore" on a worldwide basis.Includes parts needed to construct the Explore Model along with a variety of other parts for use by FLL Explore teams as they participate in the season.Additionally, this set can be combined with various WeDo 2.0 parts to create a motorized Explore Model.Please note, only one Minifigure is shown in the Instruction Manual so only one has been created for this set. However, there are other minifigure parts in the inventory.

name: PLAYMAKERS Discover Set
description: Created for use in the FIRST LEGO League Discover program during the 2020-2021 "PLAYMAKERS" season.This set rebranded the "FIRST LEGO League Jr. Discovery Edition" program into "FIRST LEGO League Discover" on a global basisIncludes parts needed to construct the Discover Model along with five sets of the program's core "Six Bricks" component.

name: CARGO CONNECT Challenge Kit
description: Created for use during 2021-2022 FIRST LEGO League Challenge "CARGO CONNECT" season. Packaged in a cardboard box containing the challenge mat and a large number of part bags.

name: CARGO CONNECT Explore Set
description: Created for use during the 2021-2022 FIRST LEGO League Explore "CARGO CONNECT" season.Includes parts needed to construct the truck and sorting factory along with a variety of other parts for use by FLL Explore teams as they participate in the season.Additionally, this set can be optionally combined with various parts to create a motorize attachment for the sorting factory using either WeDo 2.0 or SPIKE Essential.N.B.: While this set includes minifigure parts, no specific combination is specified in the building instructions encouraging FLL Explore teams to combine the parts as desired.

name: CARGO CONNECT Discover Set
description: Created for use in the FIRST LEGO League Discover program during the 2021-2022 "CARGO CONNECT" season. Includes parts needed to construct the Discover Truck Model, Discover Destination Models and Discover Sorting Center Model along with five sets of the program's core "Six Bricks" component.

name: SUPERPOWERED Challenge Kit
description: Created for use during 2022-2023 FIRST LEGO League Challenge "SUPERPOWERED" season. Packaged in a cardboard box containing the challenge mat and a large number of part bags.

name: SUPERPOWERED Explore Set
description: Created for use during the 2022-2023 FIRST LEGO League Explore "SUPERPOWERED" season.Includes parts needed to construct the “Wind Turbine Energy Source”, “Energy Storage” and “Carousel Energy User” Explore Models along with a variety of other parts for use by FLL Explore teams as they participate in the season.Additionally, this set can be optionally combined with various SPIKE Essential parts to create motorized variants. While SPIKE Essential officially replaced WeDo 2.0 as the global standard for FLL Explore this season, teams already owning WeDo 2.0 equipment were allowed to use those components to create the motorized variants.

name: SUPERPOWERED Discover Set
description: Created for use in the FIRST LEGO League Discover program during the 2022-2023 "SUPERPOWERED" season. Includes parts needed to construct the Discover Energy Source Model, the Discover Energy Storage and Distribution Model and the Discover Energy User Model along with five sets of the program's core "Six Bricks" component.

name: Pirates of the Caribbean Classic Kit
LEGO Store Special Event Minifigure Set
description:
This set was available in limited quantities during celebration events held at various LEGO Brand Stores as a gift with purchase. Due to being used at multiple events, the set does not include any on-set limited edition numbering.  Known events where this set could be obtained include:
March 23-25, 2012: Grand Opening of relocated LEGO Store in Colorado Mills, Denver, Colorado, USA
May 4-5, 2012: First Anniversary of LEGO Store in Beachwood Place in Beachwood, Ohio, USA
2012 (exact dates unknown): First Anniversary of LEGO Store in South Coast Plaza in Costa Mesa, California, USA
November 2013: Grand Opening of LEGO Store in Wijnegem, Belgium
2013 (exact dates unknown): Anniversaries of LEGO Stores in Germany
The set was also available for retail purchase from select LEGO Stores (most likely remaining unused stock) in the United States in 2013.Select sets, mostly in Europe, have been noted to reflect a set number of 6001096.

name: Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides Collection

description:
Available as a promotional giveaway during several events. Known events include:
Free to visitors to the LEGO booth at New York Toy Fair held February 12 to February 15, 2012.
Gift with purchases exceeding £20 from LEGOLAND Windsor in the United Kingdom during April 2012.
Gift with purchase of LEGO Star Wars sets from Smyths toy stores in Ireland and the United Kingdom between mid-May 2012 and June 2012 while supplies lasted.
Gift with purchase of LEGO Star Wars sets from Toys R Us locations in France. Promotion announced as running between May 29 and June 17, 2012 but sold out early at most locations due to limit of 2,000 sets for promotion at all locations.
Included in larger Sith Infiltrator commemorative tins distributed during San Diego Comic-Con between July 11 and July 15, 2012.
Free to visitors to the LEGO booth at FAN EXPO Canada held at the Metro Toronto Convention Centre in Toronto, Ontario, Canada during the “Star Wars” theme day on August 23, 2012.
Gift with purchase of LEGO Star Wars sets (minimum two required) from SMYK stores in Poland during July 2012.

description: Easy-to-use software and 12 theme-bases activities for the 9580-1 WeDo Construction set. Included site license permits installation and use of the software on all compatible computers at a purchasing institution.For the single license version, see part 2000097.In addition to sales by LEGO Education in a number of settings, this software and licensing was available to Canadian Junior FIRST LEGO League teams participating in the 2009-2010 season optional robotics pilot. Teams participating in the pilot were also required to purchase set 9580-1 to obtain the necessary components. Teams participating in the pilot from the United States, and all teams globally beginning in 2010, could obtain all needed components and licensing in a single purchase of set 5003423-1.

name: Jr.FLL Plus Kit
description: Includes activity pack materials in printed form in a binder that are were previously available digitally in part 2009580 and continued to be available in digital form on the included part 2000097.During the 2009-2010 season, this set was available exclusively to Junior FIRST LEGO League teams in the United States as part of an optional pilot expansion of the program into robotics. Teams in Canada participating in the same pilot were required to purchase the same components as two distinct sets - 9580-1 and 5003422-1.Between the 2010-2011 and 2015-2016 seasons, this set was used by all Junior FIRST LEGO League teams globally as a common season-to-season optional baseline of parts for all robotic challenges.Between the 2011-2012 and 2015-2016 seasons, an expanded version of this set was also available to teams as set 5003435-1. During the 2015-2016 season, a reduced version of the set was available to teams as set 5003826-1. Both of these variants excluded the printed materials but continued to provide that content in a digital form. This set was made available for more generalized sale by LEGO Education (outside of the Jr.FLL program) beginning in 2014 and was marketed as the “WeDo Combo”.Also known as set number 991727 under the name “Jr.FLL Robotics Kit”.

The contents are known to have varied based on stock availability - especially in Europe. The set always contained five previously issued polybags or key chains. name: DC Comics Super Heroes: Visual Dictionary
description: Celebrate the entire action-packed DC Universe of super heroes and Super-Villains with the LEGO DC Super Heroes Visual Dictionary. This comprehensive guide to LEGO DC construction toys—including THE LEGO BATMAN MOVIE sets—features full-color images of the models, characters, vehicles, weapons and gadgets, complemented by lots of fascinating facts and figures. Fans can explore every detail of the Batcave, Wonder Woman's Invisible Jet, Lex Luthor's powerful mech, the crazy rides at Jokerland and much more. Readers also get a look behind the scenes at the LEGO Group’s HQ in Billund, Denmark, and meet the team that creates such brilliant sets. name: Star Wars: The Visual Dictionary: Anniversary Edition
description:
Fans will love to delve into this fully updated and expanded visual guide to all the minifigures, vehicles and sets from the entire LEGO® Star Wars™ saga. The 160-page LEGO Star Wars Visual Dictionary features a comprehensive collection of full-color images, detailed comments, close-ups, data files and set history—plus a Beyond the Brick chapter containing concept art and an interview with the creative team behind the LEGO Star Wars franchise
Includes an exclusive Finn minifigure in his bacta suit plus 2 art prints.
This hardcover, illustrated, 160-page book features full-color images of all the minifigures, vehicles and sets from the entire LEGO® Star Wars™ saga, plus lots of facts, figures and fascinating insight.

name: Star Wars Collectible Cards
description:
These exclusive collectable cards will come in a branded envelope and include two Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back movie poster cards and a special card: either a Boba Fett™ or a TIE Fighter Pilot™ card with a gold foil finish
Special gold foil cards are randomly packed and therefore cannot be pre-selected
Each card measures 121 x 157mm and is branded with the Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back anniversary logo
The envelope measures 124mm x 165 mm and comes branded with the Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back anniversary logo
This promotion is running from 22/06/2020 to 30/06/2020
Free Exclusive Star Wars Collectible Cards offer is valid for orders online at LEGO.com only and LEGO Catalogue telephone orders from 22/06/2020 to 30/06/2020, or while stocks last. Qualifying purchase must be equal to or greater than £55 in LEGO Star Wars merchandise only. - LEGO.com

The set's building instructions serve as the boxart viewable through the open front. N.B.: While the set number is the official one on LEGO shipping invoices and promotional materials, the set has been seen with the numbers 6346097 (North America) and 6346098 (Europe) as the set number printed on front of the building instructions. name: Limited Edition Super Mario Gold Coin
description:
Available via various promotions including:
November 2020: Prize for a scratch card raffle conducted by Toys R Us stores in Hong Kong. Entry required at least HK$100 purchase. Limited to 500 sets.
March 2021: Gift with purchases exceeding AUS$70 of Super Mario theme sets from Zing Pop Culture in Australia
July and August 2021: Plans to distribute this coin along with the launch of set 71387-1 were disrupted by supply chain issues. Accordingly, various LEGO Brand Stores who received supply in time in Canada, Europe, the United Kingdom and the United States made these coins available via various distribution schemes including gift with purchase minimums, scavenger hunts and randomly.
September 6 to September 30, 2021: Gift with purchase of Super Mario theme sets exceeding AUS$99 / 5000¥ / NZ$99 / KRW 79,000 from LEGO.com or LEGO Catalogue phone orders (while supplies lasted) in Australia, Japan, New Zealand and South Korea.
March 10 to March 13, 2022 by either "Head to a participating store with your LEGO® Mario™ figure or LEGO® Luigi™ figure and wave to the LEGO Super Mario cutout in-store OR take a picture with the LEGO Super Mario cutout in-store to receive a LEGO® Super Mario™ collectible coin."

name: Swing Ship Ride
description: Available as a gift with qualifying purchases during June 2021 from LEGO Brand Stores or the LEGO Online Shop. VIP members were also able to obtain this set as a gift with purchases exceeding $85 / £85 / 85€ / 2215 Kč / 635 kr. / 27775 Ft / 860 kr / 375 zł / 95 CHF / 915 kr beginning on September 6, 2021. This promotion ended on  September 8, 2021 in North America and September 12, 2021 in Europe and the United Kingdom (both while supplies lasted). This set was originally developed to commemorate Children's Day and original promotional images show a corresponding tile. Shipping invoices accordingly refer to the set as for "C-Day". During production, a decision was made to replace this tile with one saying "LEG GODT" (Danish for "Play Well"). This was likely due to the inconsistency of observation dates of Children's Day around the world and in acceptance of global supply chain disruptions during 2021.Packaged in a pressure-sealed plastic bag inserted behind the building instructions into a open-fronted cardboard box.While the set number is the official one on LEGO shipping invoices and promotional materials, the set has been seen with the numbers 6373620, 6373621 and 9363621 as the set number on the building instructions depending on the region of release. Additionally, various LEGO regional sites and printed materials have referred to this as set 5006748.

name: Sweet Mayhem Staticker
description:
The LEGO Movie 2 Sweet Mayhem Staticker is a fun and creative adhesive-free sliding decal. Decorate a bedroom, office, play space, or locker with your favorite LEGO Movie 2 character. Staticker pieces cling to most smooth surfaces, such as walls, glass, metal, and wood. Select a surface, peel the backing film from the Staticker, and create the pose you like best for the character. 
Staticker adhesive-free sliding decals are BPA and PVC free. 
Assembled size is approximately: 14" wide x 24" tall 
Set contains 11 pieces 
Clings to most smooth surfaces Avoid placing near windows, air vents, and hot surfaces 
Fun and creative BPA and PVC free
(from shop-florida.legoland.com)

name: Sky Police Parachute Arrest
description: Patrol the LEGO City streets from above with the awesome 60208 Sky Police Parachute Arrest set, featuring a high-speed toy police jet plane with opening minifigure cockpit and extending hook to capture the working parachute toy, plus a police motorbike and getaway buggy. This action-packed police play set also includes 2 backpacks with loot and 4 minifigures. (From LEGO.com)

name: Sky Police Diamond Heist
description: Patrol the LEGO City streets from the sky with the awesome 60209 Sky Police Diamond Heist set, featuring an armored police transporter truck with opening roof, new-for-January-2019 working light and sound brick, jail cell and removable gem safe. This action-packed LEGO City police set also includes a police winged jetpack, a crook's helicopter with spinning rotors, plastic climbing rope and opening cockpit, plus 4 minifigures.(From LEGO.com)

name: Fire Chief's Car
description: Available three years later in the US as 6602.

name: Sky Police Air Base
description: Patrol the LEGO City streets from above with the highly detailed 60210 Sky Police Air Base toy set, featuring a 3-level police station control tower with jetpack storage, office on the ground floor, attached tool storage area and a jail cell with bed and breakaway wall. This fantastic set also includes a police plane with removable nose cone and hatch underneath to drop the parachute toy, a jetpack with foldable wings, a police motorbike, a getaway car with chain and hook, and 6 minifigures. (From LEGO.com)

name: Burger Bar Fire Rescue
description: Defend the local burger shop with the awesome LEGO City 60214 Burger Bar Fire Rescue set, featuring a burger bar with sign and toppling fire elements, sliding service window and trash can. This fun set also features a fire truck with minifigure cab, 2 storage compartments, rotating back end and new-for-January-2019 directional pump with ‘water jet' function. There's also a motorbike with room for a fire extinguisher, new-for-January-2019 fire axe and 3 minifigures. (From LEGO.com)

name: Fire Station
description: Protect the citizens of LEGO City with the action-packed 60215 Fire Station, featuring a 3-level fire station with office, relaxation room and scout tower, small waterside dock and a separate garage with large opening front door and a landing pad for the detachable scouting drone with spinning rotors and camera. This cool set also features a fire off-road vehicle with a stud-shooting fire hose and new-for-January-2019 working light and sound brick, plus a water scooter, 4 minifigures and a fire station dog figure. (From LEGO.com)

name: Downtown Fire Brigade
description: Protect the citizens of LEGO City with the incredible 60216 Downtown Fire Brigade set, featuring a large fire ladder truck with new-for-January-2019 working light and sound brick, extending swivel ladder and fire hose with new-for-January-2019 pump with ‘water jet' function. This thrilling set also includes a 3-level building with roof, construction area with fence, falling lamppost and a porta-toilet with removable top and front, plus a free-standing crane with rotating arm and functioning winch. There’s also a fire helicopter with opening cockpit and R.O.S.-T3 the ROV, both with a new-for-January-2019 3-stud shooter, and a motorbike with space for warning lights, and 7 minifigures. (From LEGO.com)

name: Fire Plane
description: Help the firefighters protect the forest critters of LEGO City with the exciting 60217 Fire Plane set, featuring a dual-propeller firefighting plane with pontoons, detachable minifigure cockpit, hatch on top to load the water elements and a lever to drop them. This rescue building toy set also includes a fire buggy with new-for-January-2019 3-shot stud shooter, plus 2 trees, 3 minifigures and a skunk figure. (From LEGO.com)
