name: Batman: The Attack of the Talons
Spider-Man Bike Rescue
description: LEGO reports 235 pieces for this set. The difference results from how Rebrickable inventories the web effect accessories.Speed through New York City streets and help Spider-Man and Miles Morales thwart evil Carnage’s mission to blow up the power generator in LEGO Marvel Spider-Man 76113 Spider-Man Bike Rescue. This action-packed construction toy features a Spider-Man bike with a tech spider shooter and web gun (non-shooting), and a buildable power generator with an explode function. It also includes 3 LEGO minifigures, plus 9 assorted web elements to customize your builds, minifigures and weapons for creative play. Buildable Spider-Man bike toy measures over 1” (5cm) high, 5” (13cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.Power generator measures over 1” (3cm) high, 5” (13cm) wide and 1” (5cm) deep.(From LEGO.com)

name: Spider-Man's Spider Crawler
description: LEGO reports 418 pieces for this set. The difference results from how Rebrickable inventories the web effect accessories.Team up with Spider-Man and Spider-Man 2099 to pursue diamond thieves Sandman and Vulture in the LEGO Marvel Spider-Man 76114 Spider-Man’s Spider Crawler. The Crawler features a lifelike spider-crawling function, 2 stud shooters and a shooter that fires tech spider or web elements. This superhero playset includes 4 LEGO minifigures with weapons, Sandman's buildable opening sandbase with hidden diamond elements and Vulture's buildable wings. Also includes 9 assorted web elements to customize your builds, minifigures and weapons for imaginative play. Spider-Man’s Spider Crawler buildable mech toy measures over 3” (8cm) high, 8” (22cm) long and 5” (15cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Spider Mech vs. Venom
description: LEGO reports 604 pieces for this set. The difference results from how Rebrickable inventories the web effect accessories.Join Spider-Man and Ghost Spider on a mission to release Aunt May from Venom’s clutches in a thrilling LEGO Marvel Spider-Man 76115 Spider Mech vs. Venom battle. Match the posable Spider Mech, featuring an opening minifigure cockpit, tech spider/web shooter and gripping claw, against the huge posable Venom Mech, with minifigure-grabbing claws. This superhero toy building kit includes 4 LEGO minifigures, Ghost Spider's hover board with 2 stud shooters, plus 9 assorted web elements to customize your builds, minifigures and weapons. Buildable Spider Mech toy measures over 5” (14 cm) high, 4” (11cm) long and 1” (4cm) wide.Venom Mech measures over 8” (22cm) high, 7” (18cm) long and 3” (8cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Batman Batsub and the Underwater Clash
description: LEGO reports 174 pieces for this set. The difference results from how Rebrickable inventories the wave accessories.Role-play high-speed battles against Ocean Master with this LEGO DC Batman 76116 Batman Batsub and the Underwater Clash set. This buildable Batman submarine toy features an opening bubble-shaped minifigure cockpit, adjustable claws to grab weapons, 360-degree rotating wings, stud shooters, rear rotating propellers and detachable fins to attach to Batman's feet and use as flippers. This cool Batman playset includes 3 LEGO minifigures with weapons and a shark figure, plus 10 assorted Power Burst elements to customize your builds, minifigures and weapons for unlimited imaginative play. Batsub super-hero vehicle measures over 1” (5cm) high, 8” (21cm) long and 4” (11cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Batman Mech vs. Poison Ivy Mech
description: LEGO reports 375 pieces for this set.Team up with Batman to rescue The Flash from Poison Ivy and Firefly with this action-packed LEGO DC Batman 76117 Batman Mech vs. Poison Ivy Mech building set for kids. The posable Batman Mech features an opening minifigure cockpit, dual stud shooter, spinning saw blade and a net shooter, while the Poison Ivy Mech has a minifigure cockpit, stud shooter and a collapse function. Both mechs also feature gripping hands to grab a minifigure. This awesome Batman toy includes 4 LEGO minifigures plus 10 assorted Power Burst elements to customize your builds, minifigures and weapons for endless creative play. Bat-mech measures over 6” (17cm) high, 3” (10cm) long and 7” (19cm) wide.Poison Ivy™ Mech measures over 5” (13cm) high, 2” (6cm) long and 6” (16cm) wide.

name: Batman Batwing and The Riddler Heist
Muscle Car
description: LEGO has confirmed that this set was never released. However, building instructions were made available and can be found online if you want to build this set from your own parts.

name: Iron Man Hall of Armour
description: Connects with set 76167-1.

name: Captain Marvel and The Skrull Attack
description: Team up with Captain Marvel and Nick Fury to save Goose the cat from Talos in LEGO Marvel 76127 Captain Marvel and The Skrull Attack. This action-packed construction toy features Nick Fury’s Quinjet with an opening dual minifigure cockpit, adjustable wings, 2 flick-missile shooters that each shoot 4 missiles at once, and an opening rear compartment with space for Goose. This popular toy building set for kids includes 3 minifigures with weapons to recreate exciting scenes from the Captain Marvel movie and for endless imaginative play.Quinjet measures over 4” (11cm) high, 11” (30cm) long and 8” (21cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Stark Jet and the Drone Attack
Spider-Man Car Chase
description: Give your child an exciting LEGO Marvel Spider-Man role-play experience as you help them pursue the bank-robbing Green Goblin in the 76133 Spider-Man Car Chase. This LEGO 4+ set is specially designed to be fun and easy for preschoolers and youngsters. The Spider-Man car toy building set features a minifigure cockpit and spider web string with a spider web that attaches to the Green Goblin's glider, plus a special Starter Brick base that allows even first-time builders to enjoy constructing buildings, vehicles and more, all on their own. The included simple guide to build and play will also help your budding superhero understand the purpose of the building instructions and grow their imagination and confidence to try new things in a familiar LEGO Marvel world. This simple LEGO Spider-Man playset includes 2 LEGO minifigures, Green Goblin's buildable pumpkin bomb, plus $100 banknote and money sack elements for endless creative play. Spider-Man buggy measures over 3” (9cm) high, 4” (11cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Spider-Man: Doc Ock Diamond Heist
description: Let your young superhero play out an awesome LEGO Marvel Spider-Man experience chasing Doc Ock’s getaway speedboat with Spider-Man’s flyer in the 76134 Spider-Man: Doc Ock Diamond Heist. This LEGO 4+ creative building toy, which is specially designed to be fun and easy to build for preschoolers and youngsters, features a special Starter Brick base that lets even first-time builders experience the pride of constructing buildings, vehicles and more, all on their own. The included simple guide to build and play will also help your youngster understand the purpose of the building instructions and grow their imagination and confidence to try new things in a familiar LEGO Marvel world. They’ll love building the dock with a functioning crane to lift a container, Doc Ock's speedboat with mechanical arms, and the Spider-Man flyer with a disc shooter and spider web that can attach to the speedboat or container. This simple LEGO Marvel buildable Spider-Man toy for kids also includes 3 minifigures for endless imaginative play. Dock measures over 6” (17cm) high, 5” (13cm) wide and 5” (13cm) deep.Spider-Man flyer measures over 1” (4cm) high, 5” (13cm) long and 5” (14cm) wide.Doc Ock speedboat measures over 3” (10cm) high, 4” (12cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide.(From LEGO.com)

name: Iron Man Hulkbuster versus A.I.M. Agent
Avengers Tower Battle
description: The LEGO® Marvel Avengers: Avengers Tower Battle (76166) provides kids with superhero battle action inside and outside the 5-floor Marvel Avengers Tower.Features, functions, action and adventure!Superheroes Iron Man and Black Widow take on the evil Red Skull and his A.I.M. Agents in an epic battle spread over the spectacular, 5-floor Marvel Avengers Tower. The structure opens for easy access to 7 awesome rooms where kids can enjoy endless imaginative adventures: blow out the energy core, blast open the jail, collapse the balcony, launch a rocket attack… the iconic New York skyscraper is packed with role-play possibilities with classic Marvel characters.Rooms include Black Widow’s Sky Cycle garage, the Arc Reactor room, the Armory room, a tech lab, a jail and 2 balconies. Skyfall - BMT 216A
No Time To Die - A 4269 00

name: Star Wars Magnet Set
description: No single film in the Star Wars canon included all three characters in this set simultaneously. During the Original Trilogy, Stormtroopers appear in Episodes IV, V and VI. The Y-Wing Pilot Jon "Dutch" Vander only appears in Episode IV. AT-ST Drivers only appear in Episodes V and VI. The exact driver being depicted in this set has never been identified by LEGO. However, the only minifig "AT-ST Pilot" released by LEGO prior to this set's release is Major Marquand (now known as Major Newland) from Episode VI.

Limited edition of 200 variants of the standard, 5:1 upscaled Wooden Minifigure (set 853967-1) created as a promotional item for the documentary movie Colette Mon Amour about the French fashion concept store Colette. The limited edition featuring blue hands, the store's signature two blue dots on the front and the years 1997-2017 on the rear marking the dates the store was open along with a collector's booklet and identifying sticker on the boxart.Available via the following methods:Purchase for $220 from the highsobiety.com online shop during product drop windows on December 14 and December 16, 2020
Redemption of 16,000 VIP points on December 15, 2020 (five copies available via this method)
As the prize of a sweepstakes open to VIP members in Austria , Canada (excluding Quebec), Estonia, France, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Slovakia, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom and the United States between December 15, 2020 and January 9, 2021. Entries were limited to 15 per VIP member and cost 50 points each..

name: Tractor
description: Based loosely on the "MB Trac" commercial tractors of the era (without any licensing connecting this model to a specific manufacturer), this set was sold in Canada and the United States under the name "Harvester" and under the name "Tractor" in the rest of the world.Later copies of this set (sold beginning in 1982 or 1983) replaced some parts with newer mould versions and redesigned a weak joint in the driveshaft. These changes resulted in the part inventory being reduced by 2 parts.The set's building instructions include detailed instructions for the main tractor body along with two alternative instructions for a plow or a harrow as the rear attachment (there are only sufficient parts included to build one of these attachments at a time). Additionally, the instructions include:* Detailed instructions for an off-road racing vehicle B-Model* Pictorial instructions for motorizing the tractor using either the European set 870-1 or the North American set 960-1* Detailed instructions for building three additional rear attachment options using parts from set 8710-1* Pictorial instructions for building two additional B-Models - a Dune Buggy or a Beach Bicycle

name: XL Bulk Set
description: Like many Education sets, this set has had a long release period and the set contents have varied over time. The exact year of release of this version of the set is uncertain.Despite the set’s boxart reporting a copyright of 2008, the inventory reflects the contents of a newly purchased set obtained in 2019 and contains parts which did not exist prior to 2013. For an alternate inventory, based on a set obtained in 2009, see set 9090-1.

name: Castle in the Forest
description: Available for purchase during Round 1 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.While initially planned for a limited edition production of 5,000 unnumbered sets, issues with the purchase opportunity on July 1, 2021 resulted in 10,000 sets being ordered. Shipment of these sets to European customers occurred in December 2021 / January 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in North America and Oceania were delayed until March 2022. Orders were limited to 5 per customer.

name: Mountain Windmill
description: Available for purchase during Round 2 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.Announced limited edition of no more than 10,000 sets.Pre-orders were opened for this set on November 9, 2021 and the minimum production threshold of 3,000 sets was met that same day. The purchase window remained open until December 14, 2021 and approximately 8,500 sets were actually purchased. Country-level allocation limits were imposed at the start of the purchase window but were removed mid-way through that period. Purchases were limited to one set per household.Shipment to European customers began in July 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in Australia, Canada, Japan, Mexico, New Zealand, South Korea and the United States was delayed until September 2022.

name: Modular LEGO Store
description: Available for purchase during Round 2 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.Limited edition of 10,000 sets.Pre-orders were opened for this set on November 9, 2021 and the minimum production threshold of 3,000 sets was met that same day. The purchase window was announced to remained open until December 14, 2021, however the set sold out in several countries within 24 hours and globally on November 13, 2021. Purchases were limited to one set per household.Shipment to European customers began in July 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in Australia, Canada, Japan, Mexico, New Zealand, South Korea and the United States was delayed until September 2022.

name: Great Fishing Boat
description: Available for purchase during Round 1 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program. An initially announced limited edition production run of 5,000 unnumbered sets sold out upon its initial offering on July 1, 2021. Orders for this first allotment were limited to 5 per customer. Shipment of this allotment occurred to European customers in December 2021 / January 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in North America and Oceania was delayed until March 2022. On July 7, 2021 it was announced that a second purchase opportunity of an additional 5,000 unnumbered sets would be available for purchase on August 3, 2021. This allotment again sold out within 24 hours. Orders for this second allotment were limited to 1 per customer. Shipment of this allotment occurred in June 2022.

name: Retro Bowling Alley
description: Available for purchase during Round 2 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.Announced limited edition of no more than 10,000 sets.Pre-orders were opened for this set on November 9, 2021 and the minimum production threshold of 3,000 sets was met that same day. The purchase window remained open until December 14, 2021 and approximately 9,000 sets were actually purchased. Country-level allocation limits were imposed at the start of the purchase window but were removed mid-way through that period. Purchases were limited to one set per household.Shipment to European customers began in July 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in Australia, Canada, Japan, Mexico, New Zealand, South Korea and the United States was delayed until September 2022.

name: Clockwork Aquarium
description: Available for purchase during Round 2 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.Announced limited edition of no more than 10,000 sets.Pre-orders were opened for this set on November 9, 2021 and the minimum production threshold of 3,000 sets was met that same day. The purchase window remained open until December 14, 2021 and approximately 8,000 sets were actually purchased. Country-level allocation limits were imposed at the start of the purchase window but were removed mid-way through that period. Purchases were limited to one set per household.Shipment to European customers began in July 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in Australia, Canada, Japan, Mexico, New Zealand, South Korea and the United States was delayed until September 2022.

name: Sheriff’s Safe
description: Available for purchase during Round 1 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program. An initially announced limited edition production run of 5,000 unnumbered sets sold out upon its initial offering on July 1, 2021. Orders for this first allotment were limited to 5 per customer. Shipment of this allotment to European customers occurred in December 2021 / January 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in North America and Oceania was delayed until March 2022.On July 7, 2021 it was announced that a second purchase opportunity including a maximum of an addition 5,000 unnumbered sets would be available for purchase between August 3 and August 31, 2021 (while supplies lasted and subject to various regional limits). Approximately 3,000 of these sets are reported as actually having been sold. Orders for this second allotment were limited to 1 per customer. Shipment of this allotment occurred in June 2022.In December 2021, Il Buono, the designer of the set, announced that the lock mechanism doesn't work with the pins included in the set and in the instructions. You have to exchange 10x 32002 Technic Pin 3/4 with 10x 4274 Technic Pin 1/2 to make the safe work properly. LEGO Customer Service sent the ten pins to owners of the set on demand.

name: Kakapo
description: Available for purchase during Round 1 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program.An initially announced limited edition production run of 5,000 unnumbered sets was made available for purchase beginning on July 1, 2021 and sold out in most regions within hours and in all regions by July 8, 2021. Orders for this first allotment were limited to 5 per customer. Shipment of this allotment to European customers occurred in December 2021 / January 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in North America and Oceania was delayed until March 2022.On July 7, 2021 it was announced that a second purchase opportunity including a maximum of an addition 5,000 unnumbered sets would be available for purchase between August 3 and August 31, 2021 (while supplies lasted and subject to various regional limits). Approximately 2,500 of these sets are reported as actually having been sold. Orders for this second allotment were limited to 1 per customer. Shipment of this allotment occurred in June 2022.

name: Venetian Houses
description: Originally announced as part of Round 3, this set was available for purchase during Round 2 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program after a death on the set of the movie Rust resulted in the delay of "BrickWest Studios” (the previously announced Round 2 and ultimately unsuccessful Round 3 candidate).Limited edition of 10,000 sets.Pre-orders were opened for this set on November 9, 2021 and the minimum production threshold of 3,000 sets was met that same day. The purchase window was announced to remained open until December 14, 2021, however the set sold out globally on December 4, 2021. Country-level allocation limits were imposed at the start of the purchase window but were removed mid-way through that period. Purchases were limited to one set per household.Shipment to European customers began in July 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in Australia, Canada, Japan, Mexico, New Zealand, South Korea and the United States was delayed until September 2022.

name: Pursuit of Flight
description: Available for purchase during Round 1 of the 2021 BrickLink Designer Program. An initially announced limited edition production run of 5,000 unnumbered sets was made available for purchase beginning on July 1, 2021 and sold out in most regions within hours and in all regions by July 3, 2021. Orders for this first allotment were limited to 5 per customer. Shipment of this allotment to European customers occurred in December 2021 / January 2022. Due to supply chain disruptions, shipment to customers in North America and Oceania was delayed until March 2022.On July 7, 2021 it was announced that a second purchase opportunity including a maximum of an addition 5,000 unnumbered sets would be available for purchase between August 3 and August 31, 2021 (while supplies lasted and subject to various regional limits). Approximately 2,500 of these sets are reported as actually having been sold. Orders for this second allotment were limited to 1 per customer. Shipment of this allotment occurred in June 2022.

Harley-Davidson Mini Motorcycle
description: Available as a "make-and-take" gift at a number of LEGO events held in July and August 2019 to promote set 10269-1. Known events include:* July 17, 2019 - LEGO Store in Shanghai, China (People's Square) (purchase of 10269-1 required)* July 20, 2019 - LEGO Store in Shanghai, China (Disneytown) (purchase of 10269-1 required)* July 21, 2019 - LEGO Store in Beijing, China (purchase of 10269-1 required)* July 28, 2019 - Harley Days event in Dresden, Germany* August 10, 2019 - LEGO Store in New York City, United States (Flatiron District)* August 20-30, 2019 - LEGO Store in Munich, Germany (Riem-Arcaden)Additionally, the set was available at a registration-required, in-store building event at LEGO Stores in the United States on August 6, 2019 and at LEGO Stores in the United Kingdom and Germany on August 7, 2019.Two sets of building instructions have been found. Due to the limited change presented by these instructions, the two inventories have both been attached to this set. Production numbers were reportedly limited to 3000 copies for the three Chinese events (combined). Given the widespread nature of events that occurred later, it is likely this was a limit strictly for those events and not for global release.

name: Easy Build Building Happening Rooster
description:
Known to have been used as part of interactive promotional events for Lunar (Chinese) New Year including:
Family speed building competition at Toys R Us Vivo City location in Singapore on January 7 and January 8, 2017
Family speed building competition as part of “Get Closer with Play” event at Sunway Velocity Mall in Malaysia between January 5 and January 8, 2017
Family speed building competitions held aboard an interactive mobile truck at various locations in Hong Kong between January 7 and January 15, 2017
Family speed building competition as part of “Get Closer with Play” event at Pavilion Kuala Lumpur in Malaysia between January 19 and January 22, 2017
It is known that three of the sets were awarded as prizes for each of the Malaysia events. Exact quantities, if any, which were awarded for the other events remain unknown. The parts were provided in a large plastic bag sealed with a twist tie. The building instructions were spiral bound.The build is 26cm tall x 16.5cm wide x 28.5cm deep.

Each box was sealed with an individually numbered sticker applied around the bottom edge of the box.The part count on the boxart differs with our inventory due to how Rebrickable accounts for the included spare parts.

Information about quantities produced is currently unknown but likely in the 1000-1500 set range.The minifigure is based on the TV show, DC's Legends of Tomorrow depiction of the Ray Palmer character in costume. name: LEGO Store Grand Opening Exclusive Set, So Ouest, Levallois-Perret, France
Unikitty Staticker
description:
The LEGO Movie 2 Unikitty Staticker is a fun and creative adhesive-free sliding decal. Decorate a bedroom, office, play space, or locker with your favorite LEGO Movie 2 character. Staticker pieces cling to most smooth surfaces, such as walls, glass, metal, and wood. Select a surface, peel the backing film from the Staticker, and create the pose you like best for the character. 
Staticker adhesive-free sliding decals are BPA and PVC free. 
Assembled size is approximately: 14" wide x 24" tall 
Set contains 11 pieces 
Clings to most smooth surfaces 
Avoid placing near windows, air vents, and hot surfaces 
Fun and creative BPA and PVC free.
(from shop-florida.legoland.com)

VIDIYO Tiles
description: These are all Tiles that are available in the first and second wave of VIDIYO sets. You can find the tiles you received with your set, and add them to a part list. According to research, the tiles do not completely random appear in sets. There seem to be groups of tiles, linked to specific sets. This information can help you get a higher change on finding the desired tile in a set. More details can be found in this BrickLink forum topic.The tiles in the spare parts are special BeatBits, that only come with 1 specific set.

description:
These are all the Chocolate Frogs Wizard Card tiles collectible in some 2021 and 2022 Wizarding World of Harry Potter sets. Sets containing one Wizard Card tile:
30392-1 - Hermione’s Study Desk
30435-1 - Build Your Own Hogwarts Castle
76399-1 - Hogwarts Magical Trunk
9782378891268-1 - Harry Potter: Harry’s Adventures at Hogwarts
Sets containing two Wizard Card tiles:
76386-1 - Hogwarts: Polyjuice Potion Mistake
76387-1 - Hogwarts: Fluffy Encounter
76390-1 - Harry Potter Advent Calendar 2021 (one tile each in Day 16 and Day 18)
76395-1 - Hogwarts: First Flying Lesson

76401-1 - Hogwarts Courtyard: Sirius’s Rescue

76392-1 - Hogwarts Wizard's Chess

40452-1 - Hogwarts Gryffindor Dorms
76388-1 - Hogsmeade Village Visit

To add these to your personal inventory, find the tiles you received with your sets and add them to a part list. For unopened sets containing unknown tiles, consider using part 78171.

name: Mini X-Wing Fighter
description: Available as an event-exclusive "make and take" build at the Westfield Chatswood shopping center near Sydney (Australia) during celebration events for the 20th anniversary of the LEGO Star Wars theme held on May 4, 2019. Additional information, including building instructions, is available from rebelscum.com.This build is a mini-scale model of the 16:1 scale X-Wing Fighter constructed during the same event. The super-sized build was comprised of 83,442 parts with brick-built, super-sized elements retrieved from an equally super-sized "box". The box was complete with all the decoration seen on the various 20th Anniversary Star Wars sets, a set number of 40519 (the event's date written in typical, local formatting) and the set name "World's Largest LEGO Star Wars Unboxing".

name: ZX 8000 LEGO Sneaker
description: Part of the Adidas A-ZX series of sneakers. Available is US sizes between 6 and 11.5.Features a colorful upper shaped by classic LEGO designs and topped with six lace color options (black, blue, gray, green, red and yellow). Includes LEGO studs on the heels, co-branded tongue tabs and sock liners along with six interchangeable brick lace jewels in the same colors options.Available to purchase via the Adidas app as an online release. Eligibility to purchase in the United States and Western Europe required selection via a raffle drawing conducted on 25 September 2020.Starting September 25, 2020, available while supplies last to redeem as a VIP reward for 15,600 points. Also available via a sweepstakes open to VIP members between September 25 and October 11, 2020. Individual raffles were conducted for each shoe size. Entries cost 50 VIP points and were limited to 15 entries per person per shoe size. Eligible countries for participation in raffles were Austria, Estonia, France, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Slovakia, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom and the United States.
